
[1]touch-needle

   TOUCH-NEEDLE, n. tuch'-needle. [touch and needle.] Touch-needles are
   small bars of gold, silver and copper, each pure and in all
   proportions, prepared for trying gold and silver by the touchstone, by
   comparison with the mark they leave upon it.
